---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Light as Air, Tough as Nails" description="The Hamilton Khaki Field Titanium H70205830 — lightweight, rugged, and built for the modern explorer.">
  <article class="story-article">
    <header class="story-header">
      <div class="story-category">Field & Expedition</div>
      <h1>Light as Air, Tough as Nails</h1>
      <div class="story-meta-line">
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>Hamilton</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="story-hero-img">
      <img src="https://cdnstatic.creationwatches.com/products/product-images/l/H70205830_LRG.webp" alt="Hamilton Khaki Field Titanium H70205830" />
    </div>

    <div class="story-body">
      <p class="story-lede">
        For decades, field watches have been defined by a single philosophy: do your job, no excuses. The Khaki Field Titanium takes that philosophy to its logical conclusion — the lightest, toughest Hamilton field watch ever made.
      </p>

      <h2>The Titanium Difference</h2>
      <p>
        Titanium isn't just a material choice — it's a statement. Weighing nearly 40% less than stainless steel, the H70205830 disappears on your wrist while delivering superior corrosion resistance and hypoallergenic comfort. For anyone who spends their days on the move — hiking, traveling, commuting through busy cities — that weight difference matters more than you'd think.
      </p>
      <p>
        But don't let the lightness fool you. Titanium is extraordinarily strong. This watch can handle scrapes, bumps, and the general wear-and-tear of an active lifestyle without showing it. The dark grey case has a matte finish that hides scratches beautifully, keeping the watch looking sharp year after year.
      </p>

      <h2>Field-Ready, Day or Night</h2>
      <p>
        The black dial is pure utility. Large Arabic numerals at every hour, sword-shaped hands, and generous applications of Super-LumiNova ensure you can read the time at a glance — whether you're in a dim tent at dawn or navigating a dark urban alley. The date window at 3 o'clock adds everyday practicality without cluttering the clean dial design.
      </p>
      <p>
        Inside beats an automatic movement you can trust. No batteries to replace, no quartz to fade — just the steady tick of mechanical precision. The 100-meter water resistance means you don't have to baby it. Rain, sweat, the occasional river crossing — the Khaki Field takes it all in stride.
      </p>

      <h2>An American Icon</h2>
      <p>
        Hamilton's association with military field watches dates back to World War II, when the company supplied thousands of timepieces to the U.S. armed forces. The Khaki Field collection is a direct descendant of those rugged wartime instruments. The H70205830 honors that lineage while embracing modern materials — a bridge between the past and the present, between tradition and innovation.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="story-quote">
        "The Khaki Field Titanium proves that the best tool is the one you don't notice — until you need it. Light enough to forget, tough enough to trust."
      </blockquote>

      <div class="story-specs">
        <h3>At a Glance: Hamilton Khaki Field Titanium H70205830</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Movement:</strong> Automatic (H-10 caliber, 80-hour power reserve)</li>
          <li><strong>Case:</strong> Titanium, satin-finished</li>
          <li><strong>Crystal:</strong> Sapphire with anti-reflective coating</li>
          <li><strong>Dial:</strong> Black with luminous Arabic numerals</li>
          <li><strong>Water Resistance:</strong> 100m (330ft)</li>
          <li><strong>Strap:</strong> Brown leather with contrast stitching</li>
          <li><strong>Weight:</strong> ~75g (significantly lighter than steel)</li>
          <li><strong>Price:</strong> $761.60</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="story-cta">
        <p>This piece and hundreds more are waiting to become part of your story.</p>
        <a href="/stories" class="btn">Explore More Stories</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .story-article { max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem; }
  .story-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .story-category { font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 500; }
  .story-header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-meta-line { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .story-hero-img { margin: 0 -1.5rem 3rem; text-align: center; background: var(--color-border); padding: 2rem; }
  .story-hero-img img { max-width: 300px; height: auto; }
  .story-body { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--color-text); }
  .story-lede { font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-left: 1rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent); }
  .story-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .story-quote { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; background: #f5f0e8; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text); border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; }
  .story-specs { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 2rem; background: #faf8f5; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-specs h3 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-specs ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .story-specs li { padding: 0.4rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .story-specs li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .story-cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, var(--color-border)); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-cta p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .story-article { padding: 2rem 1rem; }
    .story-header h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  }
</style>
